{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "We normalized voxel intensities in each patient to the range [0, 1].",
    "Ground truth segmentation masks for the left ventricle, myocardium, and right ventricle were available for end-diastolic and end-systolic frames All neural networks were implemented as multi-layer perceptrons (MLPs) with three hidden layers, each containing 256 neurons.",
    "Hidden layers used ReLU activation functions, unless an alternative was used, as in SIREN or FINER.",
    "Output activation functions were linear for image reconstruction and softmax for segmentation mask reconstruction.",
    "As a fitting loss L f it, we used a Huber loss in case images were fitted, and a binary cross-entropy loss in case segmentation masks were fitted."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "We normalized voxel intensities in each patient to the range [0, 1]."
  ]
}